I"<p>Presented at the 2020 Pratchett Project Conference.</p>

<p><span class="newthought">Much has been written</span>  about the incredible intertextuality and range of Terry Pratchett’s work, including his incorporation of classical literature, popular film, folk stories, music history, and even bawdy humor. Yet much remains to be explored in his works. This paper introduces an area of Pratchett Studies which has, as yet, remained largely unexplored: Pratchett’s treatment of the practice and culture of scientific disciplines.</p>
